chalkboard tariff~
The Kowloon-standard chalkboard is updated weekly by customs officials. It lists tariff rates by cargo category: raw timber, processed goods, luxury items, livestock, and sealed diplomatic pouches. A separate column shows current inspection wait times and the name of the duty officer. The formatting is precise and standardized, every letter chalked in the same careful hand.
~
E
north lantern gate~
The North Lantern Gate is constructed from massive ironpine timbers banded with iron, built to the same specifications as Kowloon's city gates but incorporating forest motifs alongside the city's standard designs. When closed, the gate blocks passage on the Lantern Road entirely. The gate mechanism is a counterweighted beam system that allows a single officer to open or close the gate.
~
